  "summary": "The issue reports pcre2grep following symlinks can lead to endless recursion when a symlink points back to a parent directory; a patch using realpath() and containment checks was proposed and tested on macOS. The maintainer commented that a modified version of the patch was applied (see ChangeLog), so this is a real functional bug that was fixed. Classification as OTHER is because this is a runtime/behavioral bug in filesystem traversal rather than a regex matching, crash, or performance bug. Discovery was manual (user-reported and tested)."
