  "log": null,
  "summary": "The report documents that using \\K inside lookaround assertions is problematic (Perl changed behavior, PCRE2 had inconsistent handling and naive implementations could loop). The maintainer implemented a change to forbid \\K in assertions by default and added a new PCRE2_EXTRA_ALLOW_LOOKAROUND_BSK option to restore the previous behavior, so this is a real semantic bug that was fixed. Classification as SEMANTIC is based on incorrect/unsafe interpretation of \\K in assertions; discovery and fix are described in the issue text (no version or commit hashes provided)."
}

