  "summary": "The report describes a JIT regression in PCRE2 10.37 where the pattern '/\\/([^\\/]+)\\/\\d+/' matches '/A/B/0' without -jit but returns \"No match\" when run with -jit. This is a real bug because the JIT produced incorrect matching behavior (semantic error) compared with non-JIT matching. The reporter reproduced it manually; a project maintainer confirmed it was fixed in version 10.38 (2021-10-01). Reproduction pattern and input are included above; logs show the failing 10.37 -jit run and the successful 10.38 -jit run."
}

